The global veno-venous extracorporeal life support devices market is segmented based on modality, application, end user, and geography. With the increasing prevalence of respiratory and cardiac diseases worldwide, the demand for such life support devices is expected to rise significantly in the forecast period. Central flow and dual-lumen modalities offer different options depending on the patient's condition, while hospitals, ambulatory surgical centers, and specialty clinics are the key end users driving market growth across various regions. Geographically, the North American and European markets are set to dominate due to advanced healthcare infrastructure and high adoption rates of novel medical technologies.

